n><br>  Posts: 71<br> <font color=#660000>(5/1/02 4:06:44 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/fcircleofsistersfrm11.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=126.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Fletching!</span><hr size=1> Another night, another tradeskill.  This one may be a bit more complicated than the other two, but I'll try to make it as simple as possible.<br>
<br>
Indifferent faction, 75 CHA, 153 INT, yadda yadda yadda.<br>
<br>
Fletching (0-102)<br>
<br>
Field Point Heads: 300 x 6c = 1800c<br>
Hooked Heads: 100 x 375c = 37500c  (!!!)<br>
<br>
Wooden Shafts: 340 x 6c = 2040c<br>
Bone Shafts: 60 x 94c = 5640c<br>
<br>
Round-cut fletchings: 300 x 6c = 1800c<br>
Parabolic-cut fletchings: 40 x 31c = 1240c<br>
Shield-shaped fletchings: 62 x 225c = 13950c<br>
<br>
Large nocks: 300 x 6c = 1800c<br>
Medium nocks: 60 x 19c = 1140c<br>
Small nocks: 40 x 50c = 2000c<br>
<br>
Total attempts: 380<br>
Total successes: 220<br>
Success rate: 57.89%<br>
Attempts per skill-up: 3.73<br>
Successes per skill-up: 2.16<br>
<br>
Total cost of supplies: 68910c<br>
<br>
Sell-backs:<br>
Field points: 15 x 4c = 60c<br>
Hooked heads: 5 x 240c = 1200c<br>
Wood shafts: 13 x 4c = 52c<br>
Bone shafts: 7 x 60c = 420c<br>
Round fletch: 15 x 4c = 60c<br>
Para fletch: 6 x 20c = 120c<br>
Shield fletch: 1 x 144c = 144c<br>
Large nocks: 8 x 4c = 32c<br>
Medium nocks: 11 x 12c = 132c<br>
Small nocks: 1 x 32c = 32c<br>
<br>
Total of sell backs: 2252c<br>
<br>
Successes (5 arrow yield):<br>
30 x 3c x 5 = 450c<br>
32 x 5c x 5 = 800c<br>
20 x 6c x 5 = 600c<br>
20 x 9c x 5 = 900c<br>
26 x 14c x 5 = 1820c<br>
35 x 26c x 5 = 4550c<br>
57 x 50c x 5 = 14250c<br>
<br>
Total money from arrows: 23370c<br>
<br>
Final cost for mastery: 43288c<br>
(Supplies - sell-backs - arrows)<br>
<br>
Notes: This method will not work for Rangers that want usable arrows while they learn to fletch.  This is one of the absolute cheapest methods to learn how to fletch.  As a result, it makes arrows that most bow-using classes wouldn't touch.  However, if you just want to get up the skill to make the really cool high-damage long-distance arrows, then this might be a viable option.<br>
<br>
I got the chart from <A HREF="http://members.bellatlantic.net/%7Eewj/fletchguide/index.htm">Aoenla's Fletching Guide</A>.  If you're a budding fletcher, it's got some great info that I'm glad I found.<br>
<br>
She also gives alternative arrows at some steps so that people who wish to pay a little more may make some arrows they can use while hunting.<br>
<br>
So, what's next for Jaranna?  Brewing?  Smithing?  Jewelcraft?  The answer is nothing.  I'll work on my Tailoring as I do all the time, but now it's time to hit the next spell circle.  And to do that, I"ll need to kill things and not spend money.  Expect an addendum when I finally do get around to getting up to the 175 skill I need. <p>Jaranna<BR>
